ce:section.ce:para:
EDX images illustrate the elemental mapping of carbon (C), oxygen (O), nitrogen (N), and sulfur (S) across the surface (
                           Figure S8
                        ) and cross-section (
                           Figure S9
                        ) of the tubular membranes. Based on the images, C and O were uniformly distributed across the surface and cross-section of the tubular membranes due to hydroxyl and carbonyl groups in the membrane. The CA and CQDs/CA tubular membranes showed no detectable nitrogen or sulfur, given that they have no amino or sulfobetaine groups. Upon introducing TQDs, the N element was detected from the tertiary amine of N-acylurea. Furthermore, adding ZQDs led to the detection of sulfur originating from the sulfobetaine group of ZQDs.
